{
  "texts": [
    "This process not only effectively removes redundancy and noise, but also enhances the model's ability to understand the graph structure at multiple levels, which is especially advantageous in tasks such as vision analysis and the prediction of chemical molecule properties.",
    "Meanwhile, by gradually reducing the number of nodes, graph pooling significantly reduces the computational complexity of large-scale graph data.",
    "It ensures that the GNN can operate efficiently with limited computational resources, overcoming the bottlenecks and memory constraints (Liu et al. 2023a). 2.",
    "Improving generalization ability: Similar to the pooling layer in convolutional neural networks, graph pooling also helps to alleviate the overfitting problem (Mesquita et al. 2020).",
    "By ignoring certain local detail information, the model pays more attention to the overall and high-level structural properties, which improves the model's ability to generalize to unseen data."
  ]
}